Description: Modern Input Method Framework
 Nimf is a lightweight, fast and extensible input method framework that supports
 various input methods and platforms.
 .
 Features:
  * Lightweight and fast input method framework
  * Supports GTK2, GTK3, GTK4, Qt5, Qt6
  * Korean input (libhangul)
  * Japanese input (anthy)
  * Chinese input (rime)
  * Optional multilingual input via separate package `nimf-i18n` (m17n)
  * System keyboard integration
  * Wayland support
  * Modern UI with system tray indicator
 .
 This package provides the core Nimf framework and the K/J/C input method
 engines (libhangul, anthy, rime).

Package: nimf-i18n
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         nimf (= ${binary:Version}),
         libm17n-0 (>= 1.7.0),
         m17n-db (>= 1.7.0)
Provides: nimf-m17n
Replaces: nimf-m17n, nimf (<< 1.3.9)
Breaks: nimf (<< 1.3.9)
Conflicts: nimf-m17n
Description: Additional multilingual engines (m17n) for Nimf
 This package contains additional multilingual input method engines based on
 m17n for Nimf, along with their icons and settings schemas. Install this to
 enable many extra languages beyond Korean, Japanese, and Chinese.


